From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 13/16] Fix Sanitize regex to reject trailing invalid content

Bug #13: The sanitizedInputRegex pattern `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+` lacks a `$`
anchor. Because .NET's Regex.IsMatch returns true as soon as any match
is found, the pattern matches only the valid prefix and silently ignores
trailing characters. For example, "abc;DROP TABLE x" passes because
"abc" satisfies the `^` anchor at position 0.

The fix adds the `$` anchor so the entire input must consist only of
valid characters.

---
diff --git a/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs b/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
index d68717e..9557ddf 100644
--- a/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
+++ b/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
@@ -1736,7 +1736,7 @@ namespace AdbcDrivers.BigQuery
             this._fileActivityListener?.Dispose();
         }
 
-        private static Regex sanitizedInputRegex = new Regex("^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+");
+        private static Regex sanitizedInputRegex = new Regex("^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$");
 
         private string Sanitize(string? input)
         {
